  "text": "2 the average power of a PRN modulated system would be increased beyond that of a typical pulsed system which will be limited by damage effects and non-linear frequency drift at high peak powers. Hence although there is a slight signal to noise (SNR) reduction in PRN modulated systems due to ambient shot noise [CITATION_1] , the increased numbers of photons sent should amply compensate for this deficiency.",
